fit into my mail slot?"

747
00:35:08,836 --> 00:35:11,422
Mom! This is all wrong!

748
00:35:11,422 --> 00:35:13,382
You're right.
It's not graphic enough.

749
00:35:13,382 --> 00:35:15,801
I'll call you back later with
the more X‐rated version.

750
00:35:15,801 --> 00:35:17,970
[ <i>Dial tone</i> ]
Wait! No, no, no, no, no.

751
00:35:17,970 --> 00:35:25,645
♪♪

752
00:35:25,645 --> 00:35:28,064
Mirren: Spend enough time
in the depths of the ocean,

753
00:35:28,064 --> 00:35:33,277
and you may eventually feel that
you are all alone in this world.

754
00:35:33,277 --> 00:35:35,237
Spend five minutes
listening to a guy

755
00:35:35,237 --> 00:35:38,032
talk about his podcast
where he rewatches every episode

756
00:35:38,032 --> 00:35:40,368
of "NCIS: New Orleans,"

757
00:35:40,368 --> 00:35:44,121
and you will wish you <i>were</i>
all alone in this world.

758
00:35:44,121 --> 00:35:47,041
But the truth is,
we are not alone,

759
00:35:47,041 --> 00:35:51,671
which is fortuitous, as life on
Earth can be full of obstacles.

760
00:35:51,671 --> 00:35:55,841
We journey now
to the Alaskan tundra

761
00:35:55,841 --> 00:35:57,802
to learn that,
in order to triumph

762
00:35:57,802 --> 00:36:00,096
over the wild's many challenges,

763
00:36:00,096 --> 00:36:05,685
the sharp‐tailed grouse must
rely on the power of teamwork.

764
00:36:05,685 --> 00:36:07,895
[ Shuffling ]

765
00:36:07,895 --> 00:36:09,438
Bird #1: Where is it?

766
00:36:09,438 --> 00:36:11,273
Bird #2:
It's in here somewhere.

767
00:36:11,273 --> 00:36:13,734
You're <i>sure</i> this is where
you last saw your phone?

768
00:36:13,734 --> 00:36:17,154
Because if we flew home and
then all the way back here...

769
00:36:17,154 --> 00:36:20,282
Yes. This is where I last
remember having it.

770
00:36:20,282 --> 00:36:21,909
Well, should we try
calling it?

771
00:36:21,909 --> 00:36:24,870
Cheryl, I‐I can't call it.
I‐I don't have my phone!

772
00:36:24,870 --> 00:36:27,415
We'll call it
with <i>my</i> phone!

773
00:36:27,415 --> 00:36:29,875
Let me guess. You didn't
set up "Find My iPhone."

774
00:36:29,875 --> 00:36:31,669
[ <i>Line ringing</i> ]
I did. I‐I did.

775
00:36:31,669 --> 00:36:33,504
I just forgot
the password!

776
00:36:33,504 --> 00:36:34,672
[ <i>Click</i> ]

777
00:36:34,672 --> 00:36:36,674
[ Glass shatters ]

778
00:36:36,674 --> 00:36:39,885
You paid for
AppleCare, right?

779
00:36:39,885 --> 00:36:48,436
♪♪

780
00:36:48,436 --> 00:36:50,354
Mirren: In the wild,
similar species,

781
00:36:50,354 --> 00:36:52,732
and temperaments,
cluster together,

782
00:36:52,732 --> 00:36:54,859
both for protection

783
00:36:54,859 --> 00:36:58,946
and occasionally to get a group
discount at the laser‐tag place.

784
00:36:58,946 --> 00:37:02,408
Whether it be a pride of lions,
a parliament of owls...

785
00:37:02,408 --> 00:37:05,619
or a crap‐ton of penguins,

786
00:37:05,619 --> 00:37:11,292
animals know that it is vitally
important to find your own gang.

787
00:37:11,292 --> 00:37:12,960
[ Upbeat music plays ]

788
00:37:12,960 --> 00:37:14,378
Made monkey:
For as long as I can remember,

789
00:37:14,378 --> 00:37:16,422
I always wanted
to be a made monkey.

790
00:37:16,422 --> 00:37:19,216
[ Accordion playing ]

791
00:37:19,216 --> 00:37:22,636
It was my big day,
the day I got <i>all</i> the bananas,

792
00:37:22,636 --> 00:37:26,056
and everybody came out
to the railing to pay respect.

793
00:37:26,056 --> 00:37:29,393
Vinnie Longtail, Tommy Bananas,
and Little Tom.

794
00:37:29,393 --> 00:37:31,937
There was Johnny "Take Your
Daughter to Work" Carbucci,

795
00:37:31,937 --> 00:37:33,189
and his daughter Claire.

796
00:37:33,189 --> 00:37:35,232
Claire:
Hi! How ya doin'?

797
00:37:35,232 --> 00:37:38,360
I saw Curious George,
Paranoid George,

798
00:37:38,360 --> 00:37:42,031
Disinterested George,
Suspiciously Curious George...

799
00:37:42,031 --> 00:37:44,533
Monkey: Hey.
What's ya PIN number?

800
00:37:44,533 --> 00:37:47,787
I was a made monkey.
I could do <i>anything.</i>

801
00:37:47,787 --> 00:37:49,830
And none of it
would have happened, kids,

802
00:37:49,830 --> 00:37:52,249
if I didn't remember to floss.

803
00:37:52,249 --> 00:37:53,918
[ Grunting ]

804
00:37:57,588 --> 00:38:05,721
♪♪

805
00:38:05,721 --> 00:38:13,521
♪♪

806
00:38:13,521 --> 00:38:15,648
Announcer:
Yes, we're <i>still</i> doing this.

807
00:38:15,648 --> 00:38:17,650
Time for another of our...

808
00:38:21,987 --> 00:38:24,240
Wolf: Honestly,
I actually think it's easier

809
00:38:24,240 --> 00:38:26,283
to pay attention
on Zoom meetings.

810
00:38:26,283 --> 00:38:28,619
I like it.
I really, really like it.

811
00:38:28,619 --> 00:38:30,496
And I'm off.

812
00:38:30,496 --> 00:38:32,414
Announcer:
This has been...

813
00:38:35,209 --> 00:38:42,091
♪♪

814
00:38:42,091 --> 00:38:45,261
Mirren: Knowing one's strengths
and limitations

815
00:38:45,261 --> 00:38:49,139
can be a helpful tool
for survival.

816
00:38:49,139 --> 00:38:53,018
Life on this planet
is chaotic and unpredictable.

817
00:38:53,018 --> 00:38:56,522
And the chacma baboon
of Botswana knows full well

818
00:38:56,522 --> 00:39:00,442
it is impossible to predict when
a new challenge will sneak up

819
00:39:00,442 --> 00:39:02,111
behind you.

820
00:39:07,157 --> 00:39:09,243
Baboon: Hey, guys,
if I ask you something,

821
00:39:09,243 --> 00:39:10,703
will you be real with me?

822
00:39:10,703 --> 00:39:12,371
‐Oh, yeah, Roy.
‐Yeah, Roy, of course.

823
00:39:12,371 --> 00:39:14,874
‐You can trust us.
‐Yeah. We'll keep it...real.

824
00:39:14,874 --> 00:39:17,376
I'm serious, guys!
Did I sit in bubble gum?

825
00:39:17,376 --> 00:39:19,879
Nathan: Turn around.
Let's see it!

826
00:39:19,879 --> 00:39:21,964
No! Oh, no!

827
00:39:21,964 --> 00:39:24,967
[ Friends laughing ]

828
00:39:24,967 --> 00:39:26,677
It's not funny!
Did I?

829
00:39:26,677 --> 00:39:28,888
[ Laughter ]

830
00:39:28,888 --> 00:39:30,931
[ Breathes deeply ]

831
00:39:30,931 --> 00:39:33,893
But, seriously,
you should see a doctor.

832
00:39:33,893 --> 00:39:37,354
♪♪

833
00:39:37,354 --> 00:39:41,483
Mirren: Let's move away
from that troubled baboon.

834
00:39:41,483 --> 00:39:43,068
And not a moment too soon.

835
00:39:43,068 --> 00:39:44,945
The image of whatever
the hell <i>that</i> was

836
00:39:44,945 --> 00:39:49,074
is gonna stick with me
for a while.

837
00:39:49,074 --> 00:39:51,660
The very survival of a species
depends upon

838
00:39:51,660 --> 00:39:57,249
that most sought‐after
of all personalities ‐‐ a mate.

839
00:39:57,249 --> 00:40:00,586
We move now
to the forests of Thailand

840
00:40:00,586 --> 00:40:04,173
to discover that even
a noble great hornbill

841
00:40:04,173 --> 00:40:07,843
can be affected
by the complications of romance.

842
00:40:07,843 --> 00:40:10,262
♪♪

843
00:40:14,600 --> 00:40:17,311
Bird: [Whimpering]
She loves me...

844
00:40:17,311 --> 00:40:19,688
[ Sobbing ]

845
00:40:19,688 --> 00:40:21,231
She loves me not...

846
00:40:21,231 --> 00:40:23,025
[ Wailing ]

847
00:40:23,025 --> 00:40:25,110
She loves me...

848
00:40:25,110 --> 00:40:26,570
[ Chuckling softly ]

849
00:40:26,570 --> 00:40:28,822
[ Moaning ]

850
00:40:28,822 --> 00:40:30,282
[ Sobbing ]

851
00:40:30,282 --> 00:40:32,034
She loves me not?!

852
00:40:32,034 --> 00:40:33,494
[ Sobbing ]

853
00:40:33,494 --> 00:40:36,914
Hey! Hey, buddy!
Relax!

854
00:40:36,914 --> 00:40:39,083
You don't know
how she feels.

855
00:40:39,083 --> 00:40:41,669
[Shakily]
She...loves me?

856
00:40:41,669 --> 00:40:43,754
Sure. It's possible.

857
00:40:43,754 --> 00:40:48,467
Although, and no offense,
but you do seem pretty needy.

858
00:40:48,467 --> 00:40:51,387
[Sobbing]
She loves me not!

859
00:40:51,387 --> 00:40:53,514
Look. I don't know!
You're asking me.

860
00:40:53,514 --> 00:40:55,724
You're asking the tree.
You're a mess, man!

861
00:40:55,724 --> 00:40:58,477
Have some self‐respect!
Damn!

862
00:40:58,477 --> 00:41:00,145
[ Sighs heavily ]

863
00:41:00,145 --> 00:41:03,357
Thank you, Jeff.
I needed that.

864
00:41:03,357 --> 00:41:06,318
Don't mention it.
You're my friend.

865
00:41:06,318 --> 00:41:09,446
[Shakily]
He...loves me?

866
00:41:09,446 --> 00:41:11,031
Whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa!

867
00:41:11,031 --> 00:41:12,950
We don't know each other
<i>that</i> well.

868
00:41:12,950 --> 00:41:15,577
[Sobbing]
He loves me not!

869
00:41:15,577 --> 00:41:19,331
Dude, get your [bleep]
together!

870
00:41:19,331 --> 00:41:23,377
♪♪

871
00:41:23,377 --> 00:41:26,463
Mirren: Our foray into the realm
of our animal friends

872
00:41:26,463 --> 00:41:28,757
now draws to a close,

873
00:41:28,757 --> 00:41:30,843
but join us next time

874
00:41:30,843 --> 00:41:33,429
as we weave around
the bend of a river...

875
00:41:33,429 --> 00:41:36,598
gaze up at a wondrous sky...

876
00:41:36,598 --> 00:41:39,518
or just watch this guy
pull something out of his ear

877
00:41:39,518 --> 00:41:41,812
and then seriously contemplate
eating it.

878
00:41:41,812 --> 00:41:45,566
Oh, my God. Please, no. Cut away
before he actually eats it!

879
00:41:45,566 --> 00:41:47,192
Thank you.

880
00:41:47,192 --> 00:41:50,320
Yes, you never know
what you'll see...

881
00:41:50,320 --> 00:41:52,406
when nature calls.

882
00:41:52,406 --> 00:41:56,577
♪♪

883
00:41:56,577 --> 00:41:58,829
[ Dance music thumping ]
Miles: Okay. That's it.

884
00:41:58,829 --> 00:42:01,665
House party's over. My mom's
gonna be home any minute.

885
00:42:01,665 --> 00:42:05,169
Hello? You two
need to leave. Now?

886
00:42:05,169 --> 00:42:07,337
Kyle: Beat it, loser. Can't you
see we're busy over here?

887
00:42:07,337 --> 00:42:09,465
I said...

888
00:42:09,465 --> 00:42:11,216
PARTY OVER!

889
00:42:11,216 --> 00:42:12,718
Kyle: Hey! We're going!

890
00:42:12,718 --> 00:42:14,887
Get out of my house!
No, no, no!

891
00:42:14,887 --> 00:42:16,680
This is my sister's room!

892
00:42:16,680 --> 00:42:18,849
Leave!
[ Frogs screaming ]

893
00:42:18,849 --> 00:42:20,309
I don't even know you!

894
00:42:20,309 --> 00:42:24,646
We're in the same
homer‐o‐o‐o‐oom!

895
00:42:24,646 --> 00:42:27,274
[ Splash ]

